author: abstractalgorithms
message:
Add comprehensive guides for Java developers transitioning to Python and Node.js

- Created a new post on advanced Python concepts for Java developers, covering decorators, generators, async/await, type hinting, data classes, context managers, higher-order functions, and list comprehensions with Java comparisons.
- Added a quick start guide for Java developers to learn Node.js, detailing core concepts, practical examples, and best practices for building scalable applications.
- Introduced a detailed guide for Java developers on Python fundamentals, including syntax, variables, control flow, functions, OOP, collections, exception handling, and file I/O with direct code comparisons.
- Implemented a deep dive into the Decorator Pattern in Java, explaining its importance, challenges, real-world applications, and providing code examples in Java, Python, JavaScript, and Node.js.
- Updated version information to reflect the latest build and commit details.
- Enhanced PostContent component to include a Table of Contents for better navigation.
